e McVey|votes=9,355|percentage=8}}{{Election box candidate with party link no change|party=Republican Party (United States)|candidate=Andy Lyons|votes=3,948|percentage=4}}{{Election box candidate with party link no change|party=Republican Party (United States)|candidate=Ann Adcook|votes=3,344|percentage=3}} {{Election box end}}\n;\n\n=== 2012 ===\n\n{{Election box begin no change\n  | title= [[United States House of Representatives elections in Indiana, 2012#District 6|Indiana's 6th Congressional District election, 2012]] <ref name=\"IED\">{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | coauthors = | title = Election Results| work = | publisher = Indiana Elections Division| date = November 28, 2012| url = http://www.in.gov/apps/sos/election/general/general2012?page=office&countyID=-1&officeID=5&districtID=-1&candidate=| doi = | accessdate = December 30, 2012 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n|party      = Republican Party (United States) \n|candidate  = ''Luke Messer''\n|votes      = 162,613\n|percentage = 59\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n|party      = Democratic Party (United States)\n|candidate  = Brad Bookout\n|votes      = 96,678\n|percentage = 35\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n|party      = Libertarian Party (United States)\n|candidate  = Rex Bell\n|votes      = 15,962\n|percentage = 6\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n|votes      = 275,253\n|percentage = 100\n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link without swing\n|winner     = Republican Party (United States)\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n=== 2014 ===\n{{Election box begin no change|title=Indiana's 6th Congressional District Election (2014)}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change|party=Republican Party (United States)|candidate=Luke Messer*|votes=102,187|percentage=65.90}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change|party=Democratic Party (United States)|candidate=Susan Hall Heitzman|vote