s wife Jennifer have two daughters and one son. Luke and Jennifer Messer are the authors of a children's book, ''Hoosier Heart''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://projects.wsj.com/campaign2012/candidates/view/luke-messer--IN-H |title=Election 2012 Luke Messer bio; The Wallstreet Journal |publisher=projects.wsj.com |accessdate=December 9, 2012}}</ref>\n\nMesser was cited for [[driving under the influence]] (DUI) in 1990 and 1996.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indystar.com/story/news/politics/2018/04/19/luke-messer-indiana-primary-2018-senate-race-didnt-disclose-duis-when-lawmaker-drunk-driving/511788002/ |title=Luke Messer didn\u2019t disclose DUIs when he replaced lawmaker killed by drunk driver |publisher=IndyStar.com |date=2018-04-19 |accessdate=2018-04-19}}</ref>\n\nFollowing Messer's election to Congress, he sold his house in [[Shelbyville, Indiana]] and moved to [[McLean, Virginia]], a [[Washington, D.C.]] suburb.<ref name=goes/> He is now listed as a registered voter at his mother's address in [[Greensburg, Indiana]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.journalgazette.net/news/local/local-politics/20170726/messer-announces-senate-bid |title=Messer announces Senate bid|last=Francisco|first=Brian|date=|work=journalgazette.net|access-date=October 4, 2017|language=en-US}}</ref> Messer has clarified that he owns the home with his mother and lives there when he is in the state.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.wibc.com/blogs/tony-katz/tony-katz-today/exclusive-messer-sets-abc-news-associated-press-straight-wifes|title=EXCLUSIVE: Messer Sets ABC News, Associated Press Straight on Wife's Employment, Living Situation {{!}} 93.1 WIBC|work=93.1 WIBC|access-date=October 4, 2017|language=en}}</ref> He faced criticism from his opponents in the 2018 Republican primary election for the [[United States Senate]] for moving his family to the Washington, D.C. area.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rollcall.com/news/home/indiana-reps-wrestle-residency|title=Indiana Reps Still Wrestling With Residency|date=September 15, 2015|website=Roll Call|access-date=July 15, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rollcall.com/news/politics/indiana-senate-primary-messer-rokita|title=Indiana Headed for Another Member-on-Member Senate Primary|date=March 23, 2017|website=Roll Call|access-date=July 15, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.journalgazette.net/blog/political-notebook/20170521/republicans-with-eye-on-senate-heat-up-their-feud|title=Republicans with eye on Senate heat up their feud {{!}} Political notebook {{!}} Journal Gazette|website=www.journalgazette.net|access-date=July 15, 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[Fishers, Indiana|Fishers]], an Indianapolis suburb, has paid Messer's wife, Jennifer Messer, $580,000 since 2015 in legal consulting she primarily does from the family's Washington, D.C. area home.<ref name=\"Indianapolis Star\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.indystar.com/story/news/politics/2017/05/11/ap-fishers-pays-rep-luke-messers-wife-20-k-month/318555001/|title=AP: Fishers pays Rep. Luke Messer's wife $20K/month|work=Indianapolis Star|access-date=June 13, 2017 |language=en}}</ref> She is paid $20,000 a month as a part-time contract attorney for the city.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cbs4indy.com/2017/06/21/ap-report-fishers-pays-rep-luke-messers-wife-240k-for-part-time-job/|title=AP report: Fishers pays Rep. Luke Messer\u2019s wife $240K for part-time job|date=June 21, 2017 |website=CBS 4 - Indianapolis News, Weather, Traffic and Sports {{!}} WTTV|access-date=June 22, 2017}}</ref> Jennifer Messer began the work for the City of Fishers two years before her husband was elected to Congress.<ref name=\"Indianapolis Star\"/> Fishers Mayor Scott Fadness said the arrangement helped usher in an era of \"unprecedented\" economic success in the growing suburb of about 85,000 people.<ref name=\"Indianapolis Star\"/><ref name=\"Indianapolis Star\"/> Messer has defended his wife's work, calling her \"the brains of the Messer outfit\", and Jennifer defended her work in an op-ed for ''[[The Indianapolis Star]]'', calling an [[Associated Press]] story about her \"unfair, intellectually dishonest and straight-up sexist\".<ref name=\"rollcall.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.rollcall.com/news/politics/messer-defends-wifes-contract-city|title=Messer Defends Wife\u2019s $20K a Month Contract With City|date=May 12, 2017 |website=Roll Call|access-date=June 13, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.indystar.com/story/opinion/2017/05/15/jennifer-messer-i-work-diligently-fishers/323033001/|title=Jennifer Messer: 'I work diligently for Fishers'|work=Indianapolis Star|access-date=June 22, 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons cat}}\n* [http://messer.house.gov/ Congressman Luke Messer] official U.S. House website\n* [http://www.lukemesser.com/ Luke Messer for Congress]\n* {{Dmoz|Regional/North_America/United_States/Indiana/Government/Federal/US_House_of_Representatives/Luke_Messer_%5BR-6%5D}}\n* {{C-SPAN|allenmesser}}\n* {{CongLinks | congbio=M001189 | votesmart=33997 | fec=C00460667 | congress=luke-messer/2130 }}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|us-hs}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Mike Pence]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of the [[List of United States Representatives from Indiana|U.S. House of Representatives]]<br>from [[Indiana's 6th congressional district]]|years=2013\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n|-\n{{s-ppo}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[James Lankford]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Chair of the [[Steering and Policy Committees of the United States House of Representatives|House Republican Policy Committee]]|years=2015\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n|-\n{{s-prec|usa}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Grace Meng]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Seniority in the United States House of Representatives|United States Representatives by seniority]]|years=281st}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Markwayne Mullin]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{IN-FedRep}}\n{{US House leaders current}}\n{{IndianaUSRepresentatives}}\n{{USHouseCurrent}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Messer, Luke}}\n[[Ca